column1: Note: "FIPStxt" refers to the State-county FIPS code. Defintions of "Rural-urban Continuum Code, 2013" may be found on the ERS website under Data Products > Rural-Urban Continuum Codes > Documentation. Counties that did not exist when the 2013 codes were determined will have missing data for this variable. Counties that were created or merged may not have complete data over the 1990-2020 period.

Source: USDA, Economic Research Service using data from the U.S. Department of Commerce, Bureau of the Census, 1990 corrected decennial census population file, 2000 population estimates base file, 2010 PL-94 summary file, and 2020 PL-94 summary file.
